annotation: Inanwatan, Duriankare and Kokoda Kasueri borrowed aruɁɔ/aru/ˈ ɾaɾɔ via Onin Patipi ˈ ɾaɾa ‘blood’ (cf. Indonesian darah)
Irarutu has gane ‘mouth’ (Voorhoeve 1995). The direction of the borrowing is not clear, but most likely from eastern SBH languages to Irarutu
